landholdings, by allowing some land redistribution while opposing nationalisation of church and monastery land;<ref name=SERAPHTIKAS/>{{#tag:ref|\"His most dramatic clash came in the mid-1980s when late Socialist Premier Andreas Papandreou tried to expropriate the Church's vast land holdings. Seraphim eventually won the battle and in retaliation [[Excommunicate#Eastern Orthodox churches|excommunicated]] seven government officials.\"<ref>Stephen McGregor. ''\"Archbishop Seraphim\".'' The Herald (Glasgow). 11 April 1998. p.19.</ref>|group=note}} on [[August 19 (Eastern Orthodox liturgics)|August 19]] Patr. [[Patriarch Pimen I of Moscow|Pimen of Moscow and All Russia]], and Ec. Patr. [[Patriarch Demetrios I of Constantinople|Demetrios I of Constantinople]] co-celebrated the [[Divine Liturgy]] on the [[Feast of the Transfiguration]] at the [[Trinity Lavra of St. Sergius|Holy Trinity St. Sergius Monastery]], being the '''first concelebration in 398 years (since January 1589)'''.<ref>John Garrard and Carol Garrard. ''Russian Orthodoxy Resurgent: Faith and Power in the New Russia.'' Princeton University Press, 2008. p. 1.</ref>\n*1988 Canonization of [[Eustathius of Thessalonica]] (\u20201197);<ref>Great Synaxaristes: {{in lang|el}} ''[http://synaxarion.gr/gr/sid/697/sxsaintinfo.aspx \u1f49 \u1f0d\u03b3\u03b9\u03bf\u03c2 \u0395\u1f50\u03c3\u03c4\u03ac\u03b8\u03b9\u03bf\u03c2 \u1f41 \u039a\u03b1\u03c4\u03ac\u03c6\u03bb\u03c9\u03c1\u03bf\u03c2 \u1f08\u03c1\u03c7\u03b9\u03b5\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03ba\u03bf\u03c0\u03bf\u03c2 \u0398\u03b5\u03c3\u03c3\u03b1\u03bb\u03bf\u03bd\u03af\u03ba\u03b7\u03c2].'' 20 \u03a3\u03b5\u03c0\u03c4\u03b5\u03bc\u03b2\u03c1\u03af\u03bf\u03c5. \u039c\u0395\u0393\u0391\u03a3 \u03a3\u03a5\u039d\u0391\u039e\u0391\u03a1\u0399\u03a3\u03a4\u0397\u03a3.</ref> Mount Athos<ref>''[https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/454 Mount Athos].'' \u00a9 UNESCO World Heritage Centre 1992\u20132012.</ref> and the [[Meteora]]<ref>''[https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/455 Meteora].'' \