rch 1992. Spiritual daughter to Fr. Amphilochios Makris the Elder.|group=note}} and Chrysanthi of Andros;<ref>Mother Nectaria McLees. ''Righteous Chrysanthi of Andros (+ 1992).'' Evlogeite, A Pilgrim's Guide to Greece. St. Nicholas Press, Kansas City, MO, 2002. pp. 96-100.</ref> the total congregation of the [[Greek Orthodox Church of Jerusalem|Patriarchate of Jerusalem]] in 1992 was estimated at 145,000 Greek Orthodox Palestinians in the [[Israeli-occupied territories|Occupied Territories]], [[Israel]] and [[Jordan]], representing the largest Christian congregation in historic Palestine, and Jerusalem in particular.<ref>Sotiris Roussos. ''THE PATRIARCHATE OF JERUSALEM IN THE GREEK-PALESTINIAN-ISRAELI TRIANGLE: IS THERE A PLACE FOR IT?'' Athens, 1 March 2003. pp. 3, 13.</ref>\n*1993 [[Cypriot Orthodox Church|Church of Cyprus]] condemned Freemasonry as a religion incompatible with Christianity;<ref>{{in lang|el}} \u039c\u03b9\u03c7\u03b1\u03ae\u03bb \u039c. ''\u0397 \u03a3\u03c5\u03bd\u03c9\u03bc\u03bf\u03c3\u03af\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u039a\u03cd\u03c0\u03c1\u03bf. \u03a3\u03b9\u03c9\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2-\u039c\u03b1\u03c3\u03bf\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2.'' \u039a\u03cd\u03c0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c2 1993. \u0392\u0384\u0388\u03ba\u03b4\u03bf\u03c3\u03b7 2003.</ref> [[Joint International Commission for Theological Dialogue Between the Catholic Church and the Orthodox Church|Orthodox-Roman Catholic Joint Theological Commission]] meets in Balamand, Lebanon, issuing common document ''\"Uniatism: Method of Union of the Past, and Present. Search for Full Communion\"'' (the '''\"[[Balamand declaration]]\"'''),<ref>''\"[https://www.vatican.va/roman_curia/pontifical_councils/chrstuni/ch_orthodox_docs/rc_pc_chrstuni_doc_19930624_lebanon_en.html TEXT: UNIATISM, METHOD OF UNION OF THE PAST, AND THE PRESENT SEARCH FOR FULL COMMUNION]\".'' JOINT INTERNATIONAL COMMISSION FOR THE THEOLOGICAL DIALOGUE BETWEEN THE ROMAN CATHOLIC CHURCH AND THE ORTHODOX CHURCH: SEVENTH PLENARY SESSION. Balamand school of theology (Lebanon) June 17\u201324, 1993.</ref> equating the Orthodox and Roman Catholics as \"sister churches\", and concluding that [[rebaptism]] should be avoided, while \"'uniatism' can no longer be accepted either as a method to be followed nor as a model of the unity our Churches are seeking\".{{#tag:ref|This declaration was roundly criticized in Orthodox literature:\n:* ''[http://orthodoxinfo.com/ecumenism/balamand.pdf THE BALAMAND UNION: A Victory of Vatican Diplomacy].'' '''CENTER FOR TRADITIONALIST ORTHODOX STUDIES''', St. Gregory Palamas Monastery, Etna, CA. July\u2013September, 1993. (pdf)\n:* ''[http://orthodoxinfo.com/ecumenism/paphagfr.pdf Papism, the Hagiorite Fathers, and the Aftermath of the \"Balamand Union\"].'' Transl. from the Greek by Patrick G. Barker. '''Hagios Kyprianos''', no. 258 (January\u2013February 1994), pp. 211-215. (pdf)\n:* ''[http://orthodoxinfo.com/ecumenism/athos_bal.aspx Letter to the Ecumenical Patriarch Concerning the Balamand Agreement].'' '''Orthodox Christian Information Center'''. Retrieved: 20 August 2016. (From: ''Orthodox Life'', Vol. 44, No. 4, July\u2013August 1994, pp. 26-39).|group=note}}\n\n*1994 Death of Elder '''[[Elder Paisios|Paisios (Eznepidis)]] of Mt. Athos''', 12 July;<ref>Herman A. Middleton. ''[http://www.orthodoxinfo.com/praxis/preciousvessels.aspx Precious Vessels of the Holy Spirit: The Lives & Counsels of Contemporary Elders of Greece].'' 2nd Ed. Protecting Veil Press, 2004. pp.124\u2013143.</ref> Greek Parliament passes a resolution marking 19 May as \"[[Greek genocide|Pontus Genocide]] Remembrance Day\";<ref>''Pontus genocide monument overshadows relations between Turkey and Greece: Turkish FM.'' '''Xinhua General News Service'''. 12 May 2006 Friday 8:30 AM EST.</ref> the Liaison Office of the Orthodox Church to the European Union was established in Brussels by the [[Ecumenical Patriarchate of Constantinople#The Holy and Sacred Synod|Holy Synod of 