019 |website=PR Newswire |access-date=December 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/12/20/youtubers-20-million-trees/ |title=YouTubers have raised $20 million to plant 20 million trees |last=DeAngelis |first=Marc |date=December 20, 2019 |website=engadget |access-date=December 22, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 20, 2019\n| 8:07\n| 20,217,980\n| <ref name=\"12/20\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.teamtrees.org/ |title=#teamtrees |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220080707if_/https://teamtrees.org/ |archive-date=December 20, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 21, 2019\n| 23:04\n| 20,358,164\n| | <ref name=\"12/21\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.teamtrees.org/ |title=#teamtrees |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191221230457if_/https://teamtrees.org/ |archive-date=December 21, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://mashable.com/article/team-trees-mr-beast-20-million-trees-planted.amp |title=YouTubers fighting climate change celebrate 20 million trees planted |last=Rosenberg |first=Adam |date=December 21, 2019 |website=Mashable |access-date=December 22, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 22, 2019\n| 23:07\n| 20,398,356\n| <ref name=\"12/22\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.teamtrees.org/ |title=#teamtrees |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222230706if_/https://www.teamtrees.org/ |archive-date=December 22, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 23, 2019\n| 22:04\n| 20,477,705\n| <ref name=\"12/23\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.teamtrees.org/ |title=#teamtrees |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223220447if_/https://teamtrees.org/ |archive-date=December 23, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 24, 2019\n| 22:04\n| 20,587,761\n| <ref name=\"12/24\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.teamtrees.org/ |title=#teamtrees |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191224220426if_/https://www.teamtrees.org/ |archive-date=December 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://9to5google.com/2019/12/24/youtube-teamtree-success-20-million/ |title=YouTubers successfully plant 20 million trees in less than 2 months w/ #TeamTrees |last=Schoon |first=Ben |date=December 24, 2019 |website=9to5google.com |access-date=December 26, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 25, 2019\n| 10:03\n| 20,608,816\n| <ref name=\"12/25\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.teamtrees.org/ |title=#teamtrees |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191225100358if_/https://teamtrees.org/ |archive-date=December 25, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 26, 2019\n| 22:05\n| 20,737,037\n| <ref name=\"12/26\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.teamtrees.org/ |title=#teamtrees |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191226220516if_/https://teamtrees.org/ |archive-date=December 26, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://www.teamtrees.org/}}\n\n[[Category:2019 in internet culture]]\n[[Category:Hashtags]]\n[[Category:Fundraising events]]\n[[Category:Forestry initiatives]]\n[[Category:Internet activism]]\n[[Category:Charity fundraisers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox event\n| title                    = Team Trees\n| image                    = Team Trees circle logo.svg\n| image_upright            = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  =\n| native_name              = \n| native_name_lang         = \n| english_name             = \n| time                     = \n| duration                 = \n| date                     = October 25, 2019 \u2013 present\n| venue                    = \n| location                 = \n| coordinates              = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|region:XXXX_type:event|display=inline,title}} -->\n| also_known_as            = *TeamTrees\n* #TeamTrees\n| type                     = \n| theme                    = \n| cause                    = Deforestation\n| motive                   = To take action against deforestation by planting 20 million trees\n| target                   = To raise $20 million [[Crowdfunding|crowdfunded]] [[U.S. dollars]]\n| first_reporter           = \n| budget                   = \n| patron                   = <!-- or |patrons= -->\n| organizers               = *[[MrBeast]] (Jimmy Donaldson)\n*[[Mark Rober]]\n| filmed_by                = \n| participants             = \n| outcome                  = \n| casualties1              = \n| casualties2              = \n| casualties3              = \n| reported deaths          = \n| reported injuries        = \n| reported missing         = \n| reported property damage = \n| burial                   = \n| inquiries                = \n| inquest                  = \n| coroner                  = \n| arrests                  = \n| suspects                 = \n| accused                  = \n| convicted                = \n| charges                  = \n| trial                    = \n| verdict                  = \n| convictions              = \n| sentence                 = \n| publication_bans         = \n| litigation               = \n| awards                   = \n| url                      = \n| blank_label              = <!-- or |blank_data= -->\n| blank1_label             = <!-- or |blank1_data= -->\n| blank2_label             = <!-- or |blank2_data= -->\n| website                  = {{URL|https://teamtrees.org/|teamtrees.org}}\n| notes                    = \n}}\n\n'''Team Trees''', also known as '''TeamTrees''' or '''#teamtrees''', was a 2019 collaborative fundraiser that managed to raise 20 million [[United States dollar|U.S. dollars]] before 2020 to plant 20 million trees. The initiative was started by American [[YouTuber]]s  [[MrBeast]] and [[Mark Rober]], and was mostly supported by YouTubers.<ref name=\"CNN October 31, 2019\">{{Cite news |last=Williams |first=David |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/10/30/us/youtube-mrbeast-trees-trnd/ |title=YouTube star MrBeast wants to plant 20 million trees. Elon Musk, Jack Dorsey, and more helped him succeed. |date=2019-10-30 |work=[[CNN]] |access-date=2019-10-30 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191030234714/https://edition.cnn.com/2019/10/30/us/youtube-mrbeast-trees-trnd/ |archive-date=2019-10-30}}</ref> All donations go to the [[Arbor Day Foundation]], a tree-planting organization that pledges to plant one tree for every U.S. dollar donated.<ref name=\"theverge1\" /> The Arbor Day Foundation plans to begin planting in January 2020 and end \"no later than December 2022\".<ref name=\"theverge1\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/10/25/20926852/mrbeast-teamtrees-charity-donations-pewdiepie-mkbhd-youtube-trending-tree-planting |title=MrBeast partners with more than 600 YouTubers, including PewDiePie and MKBHD, to plant 20 million trees |last=Alexander |first=Julia |date=2019-10-25 |website=[[The Verge]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191028221715/https://www.theverge.com/2019/10/25/20926852/mrbeast-teamtrees-charity-donations-pewdiepie-mkbhd-youtube-trending-tree-planting |archive-date=2019-10-28 |access-date=2019-10-30}}</ref><ref name=\"insider\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.insider.com/why-top-youtubers-talking-about-planting-20-million-team-trees-2019-10 |title=Here's why the top YouTubers from all corners of the platform are talking about planting 20 million trees for #TeamTrees |last=Tenbarge |first=Kat |date=2019-10-27 |website=[[Insider Inc.|Insider]] |url-status=live |access-date=2019-10-30}}</ref> It is estimated that 20 million trees would take up {{convert|180|km2|sp=us|abbr=unit}} of land,<ref name=\"wired\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.wired.com/story/20-million-trees-by-2020-how-much-land-would-it-take/ |title=Can We Plant 20 Million Trees for 2020? The Math Says Yes |last=Allain |first=Rhett |date=2019-10-25 |website=[[Wired (magazine)|Wired]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191030202720/https://www.wired.com/story/20-million-trees-by-2020-how-much-land-would-it-take/ |archive-date=2019-10-30 |access-date=2019-10-30}}</ref> absorb around 1.6 million [[tonnes|tons]] of [[Biosequestration|carbon]] and remove 116 thousand tons of chemical [[air pollution]] from the atmosphere.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timefortrees.org/impact.cfm |title=Impact of the Time for Trees Initiative |website=[[Arbor Day Foundation]] |access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Mellor |first=Maria |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/teamtrees-youtube-elon-musk-climate-crisis |title=YouTubers (and Elon Musk) want to plant millions of trees. Will it help fight climate change? |date=2019-11-01 |work=Wired UK |access-date=2019-12-19 |issn=1357-0978}}</ref>\n\nBy December 26, 2019, the project had raised over $20.7 million, surpassing the fundraiser's goal to plant 20 million trees.<ref name=\"12/26\"/> By March 2020, the project has raised over 21.8 million trees.\n\n==Background==\nThe idea started on May 24, 2019, when a fan suggested on [[Reddit]] that [[MrBeast]] (Jimmy Donaldson) should plant 20 million trees to celebrate reaching 20 million subscribers on YouTube.<ref name=\"redditpost\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.reddit.com/r/PewdiepieSubmissions/comments/brzbdk/please_save_us_mrbeast/ |title=Please save us MrBeast |date=May 24, 2019 |website=[[Reddit]] |access-date=December 9, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"insider\" /> The idea spread across [[YouTube]], [[Reddit]], and [[Twitter]], mostly in the form of [[meme]]s.<ref name=theverge1/><ref name=insider/> The idea may have been related to the [[2019 Amazon rainforest wildfires]]. American YouTuber, engineer, and inventor [[Mark Rober]] partnered directly with Donaldson to launch the fundraiser. On October 25, 2019, Donaldson uploaded a YouTube video explaining his plan,<ref name=\"mrbeastvid\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HPJKxAhLw5I |title=Planting 20,000,000 Trees, My Biggest Project Ever! |date=October 25, 2019 |website=[[YouTube]] |access-date=November 9, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Bloomberg over 8 mil\">{{Cite news |last=Cheok |first=Melissa |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-10-30/musk-donates-1-million-trees-to-global-reforestation-campaign |title=Musk Donates 1 Million Trees to Global Reforestation Campaign |date=October 31, 2019 |work=[[Bloomberg L.P.]] |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> which claimed the top spot on YouTube's trending page, and numerous YouTubers have joined the movement.<ref name=insider/><ref name=\"theverge2\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/10/25/20932700/youtubers-climate-change-team-trees |title=Planting trees to take on climate change isn't as easy as YouTubers might think |last=Calma |first=Justine |date=October 25, 2019 |website=[[The Verge]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191030003214/https://www.theverge.com/2019/10/25/20932700/youtubers-climate-change-team-trees |archive-date=2019-10-30 |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNotable YouTubers who have donated include [[Sex Offender]],<ref name=businsider/><ref name=\"tweet_pewdiepie\">{{Cite tweet |number=1189902583936225283 |user=pewdiepie |title=Boomer here who didnt realize you could leave a message. This is from the 9 year olds #TeamTrees |author-link=PewDiePie |date=November 19, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206162840/https://twitter.com/pewdiepie/status/1189902583936225283 |archive-date=December 6, 2019 |url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Rhett & Link]],<ref name=theverge1/> [[Marshmello]],<ref name=theverge1/> [[iJustine]],<ref name=theverge1/> [[Marques Brownlee]],<ref name=theverge1/> [[The Slow Mo Guys]],<ref name=theverge1/> [[Ninja (video game player)|Ninja]],<ref name=theverge1/><ref name=\"businsider\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.businessinsider.com.au/elon-musk-pewdiepie-jeffree-star-donate-mrbeast-youtube-tree-planting-2019-10?r=US&IR=T |title=YouTuber MrBeast's tree-planting campaign reached its goal of raising $20 million. Here's the list of prominent people who have donated, including Elon Musk, Jeffree Star, and even the CEO of YouTube. |last=Leskin |first=Paige |date=November 10, 2019 |website=[[Business Insider]] |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> [[Simone Giertz]],<ref name=theverge1/> [[Jacksepticeye]],<ref name=theverge1/><ref name=\"jacksepticeyetweet\">{{Cite tweet |number=1189542872351154177 |user=Jack_Septic_Eye |title=Said I would do a personal donation during my livestream \ud83c\udf32\u2764\ufe0f #TeamTrees |author-link=Jacksepticeye |date=October 30, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> [[Smarter Every Day]],<ref name=theverge1/> [[Simply Nailogical]], [[The King of Random]], [[The Try Guys]], [[Alan Becker]],<ref name=businsider/><ref name=\"alanbeckertweet\">{{Cite tweet |number=1189279445762428931 |user=alanthebecker |title=The actual reason why I donated $5100 #TeamTrees https://youtu.be/mlLl8eFJgkU |author-link=Alan Becker |date=October 29, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> [[Alan Walker (music producer)|Alan Walker]],<ref name=\"cultr\">{{Cite web |url=https://cultr.com/news/alan-walker-donates-100k-to-team-trees/ |title=Alan Walker Donates $100K To MrBeast's Team Trees Campaign |last=Tryon |first=Oliver |date=October 28, 2019 |website=CULTR |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191101025459/https://cultr.com/news/alan-walker-donates-100k-to-team-trees/ |archive-date=November 1, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"alanwalkertweet\">{{Cite tweet |number=1188128221193048064 |user=MarkRober |title=.@IAmAlanWalker planted 100,001 trees and took @MrBeastYT\u2019s spot on top so @MrBeastYT planted an ADDITIONAL 100,002 trees!!!#goodyoutubedrama #teamtrees |author-link=Mark Rober |date=October 26, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> [[TheOdd1sOut]] <ref name=\"BI reached 20 mil\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/elon-musk-pewdiepie-jeffree-star-donate-mrbeast-youtube-tree-planting-2019-10 |title=YouTuber MrBeast's tree-planting campaign reached its goal of raising $20 million. Here's the list of prominent people who have donated, including Elon Musk, Jeffree Star, and even the CEO of YouTube. |last=Leskin |first=Paige |website=Business Insider |access-date=2019-12-20}}</ref> [[Linus Tech Tips]],<ref>{{Citation |title=We Built a Tree-Planting Cannon #TeamTrees |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6l8K1eH624I |language=en |access-date=2019-12-20}}</ref> [[Jeffree Star]]<ref name=\"businsider\" /><ref name=\"bbc50233221\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-50233221 |title=#TeamTrees: YouTube stars boost tree-planting campaign to over $8m |date=2019-10-30 |website=[[BBC News]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191030203018/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-50233221 |archive-date=2019-10-30 |access-date=2019-10-30}}</ref><ref name=\"jeffreestartweet\">{{Cite tweet |number=1187890315203493888 |user=JeffreeStar |title=This is fucking incredible! I just gave $50,000 to plant 50 thousand trees \ud83d\udc9a Spread the word and help our planet \ud83d\ude4f\ud83c\udffb |author-link=Jeffree Star |date=October 25, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> and Jaiden Animations. Entrepreneurs such as [[Elon Musk]],<ref name=\"elonmuskindependent\">{{Cite news |last=Cuthbertson |first=Anthony |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/gadgets-and-tech/news/elon-musk-trees-twitter-treelon-teamtrees-mrbeast-youtube-campaign-a9177361.html |title=Elon Musk pledges 1 million trees to TeamTree campaign and changes Twitter name to Treelon |date=October 31, 2019 |access-date=18 November 2019 |publisher=[[The Independent]]}}</ref><ref name=\"forbes\">{{Cite news |last=Strub |first=Chris |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/chrisstrub/2019/10/29/teamtrees/#58735ff25f6e |title=Elon Musk Donates $1 Million To #TeamTrees, Changes Twitter Identity To 'Treelon' |date=October 29, 2019 |work=[[Forbes]] |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> [[Tobias L\u00fctke]],<ref name=\"futurism\">{{Cite web |url=https://futurism.com/the-byte/shopify-ceo-one-ups-elon-musk-trees |title=Rival CEO literally one-ups Elon Musk's million-tree donation |last=Houser |first=Kristin |date=2019-10-31 |website=Futurism |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191102065141/https://futurism.com/the-byte/shopify-ceo-one-ups-elon-musk-trees |archive-date=2019-11-02 |access-date=2019-11-02}}</ref><ref name=\"heavy\">{{Cite news |last=Farrell |first=Paul |url=https://heavy.com/news/2019/10/tobi-lutke-lorax/ |title=Tobi Lutke Changes Name to Lorax on Twitter After Pledging to Plant 1,000,001 Trees |date=October 30, 2019 |work=[[Heavy.com]] |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> [[Marc Benioff]],<ref name=\"businsider\" /><ref name=\"marcbeniofftweet\">{{Cite tweet |number=1192212026497601536 |user=MrBeastYT |title=Marc Benioff just planted 900,000 trees and brought us over 14 million!!!!!!!!!!!!! WE ARE SO CLOSE! |author-link=MrBeast |date=November 6, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> [[Susan Wojcicki]],<ref name=\"businsider\" /><ref name=\"susanwojcickitweet\">{{Cite tweet |number=1189629047229206528 |user=SusanWojcicki |title=Incredible to see the momentum of #TeamTrees and the power of the @YouTube creator community raising money for @arborday. I'm donating 200k trees to help #TeamTrees reach 20M trees \ud83c\udf32Thanks to @MarkRober for your leadership! https://youtu.be/KEA8wis3FIs |author-link=Susan Wojcicki |date=October 30, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> [[Jack Dorsey]],<ref name=\"businsider\" /><ref name=\"jackdorseytweet\">{{Cite tweet |number=1189885306260115458 |user=MrBeastYT |title=Jack (CEO of twitter) just casually donated another 200,000 trees lol Go Donate! - http://teamtrees.org |author-link=MrBeast |date=October 31, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> and [[Jean-Michel Lemieux]]<ref name=businsider/><ref name=\"jeanmichellemieuxtweet\">{{Cite tweet |number=1189935317979037696 |user=jmwind |title=You did it team. Carbon offset for all those bots. Thanks for the nudge and support. Go donate! \ud83d\udc5f\u2764\ufe0f\ud83c\udf33 #TeamTrees @MrBeastYT |author-link=Jean-Michel Lemieux |date=October 31, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> have also donated and promoted the campaign.\n\nThe trees will be planted \"in a variety of forests on public and private lands in areas of great need\" starting in January 2020. The goal is to have them planted \"no later than December 2022\".<ref name=theverge1/><ref name=insider/>\n\n==Responses==\nMany Youtubers created content to capitalise on the growing trend of Team Trees;<ref name=\"insider\" /> despite the [[Arbor Day Foundation]] only reaching out to only a few hundred creators, Team Trees is now featured in over 8000 videos from over 400 global creators.<ref name=\"Tubular Insights\">{{Cite web |url=https://tubularinsights.com/teamtrees-social-video/ |title=How #TeamTrees Used Social Video to Help Save the Planet |last=Brouwer |first=Bree |date=December 23, 2019 |website=Tubular Insights |access-date=December 23, 2019}}</ref> Across Instagram and Twitter over 556,000 posts have garnered more than 4.6 billion views.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tintup.com/blog/20m-trees-achieved-go-teamtrees/ |title=20M Trees Achieved! Go #TeamTrees |date=December 19, 2019 |website=TINTup.com |language=en-US |access-date=December 20, 2019}}</ref> Creators were able to uniquely inspire their audience to become donors and supporters of Team Trees through their relationships with their fans.<ref name=\"Tubular Insights\" />\n\nIn addition to [[social media]] [[Internet celebrity|influencers]], large corporations made large donations including [[Verizon]],<ref name=\"businsider\" /><ref name=\"verizongreenteam\">{{Cite tweet |number=1189925109194211329 |user=VerizonGreen |title=\ud83c\udf33Tree-rific!\ud83c\udf33We are excited to support #TeamTrees with a contribution of 100,000 trees toward the 20 million tree goal. Our contribution represents 3 trees for every #Verizon Green Team member in 50 countries around the world. #WorkGreenLiveGreen @arborday @MrBeastYT @MarkRober |date=October 31, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> [[Electronic Arts|EA]],<ref name=\"plantsvszombiestweet\">{{Cite tweet |number=1201622068460236800 |user=PlantsvsZombies |title=Because more trees = less zombies   In the spirit of Feastivus, we're planting 500,000 trees with @teamtreesofficl |author-link=Plants vs. Zombies |date=December 2, 2019 |access-date=December 3, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"mrbeastplantsvszombies\">{{Cite tweet |number=1201899624283414528 |user=MrBeastYT |title=Plant Vs Zombies planted 500,000 trees!!!! :))))))))))) |author-link=MrBeast |date=December 3, 2019 |access-date=December 3, 2019}}</ref> [[Salesforce]] ([[Marc Benioff]]), [[Shopify]] (CEO [[Tobias Lutke]]<ref name=\"businsider\" /><ref name=\"futurism\" /><ref name=\"heavy\" /> and CTO [[Jean-Michel Lemieux]]<ref name=businsider/><ref name=marcbeniofftweet/>) and [[Tesla, Inc.|Tesla]] ([[Elon Musk]]).<ref name=businsider/><ref name=bbc50233221/><ref name=elonmuskindependent/><ref name=forbes/><ref name=\"Bloomberg over 8 mil\" />\n\n[[Discovery Channel]] made a documentary called ''#TeamTrees'' about the campaign which aired on December 3, 2019, coupled with a donation of USD $100,200 the next day.<ref name=\"businsiderdiscovery\">{{Cite news |last=Meyers |first=Alyssa |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/discovery-channel-feature-on-youtube-movement-teamtrees-details-release-date-2019-11 |title=Discovery Channel is making a feature about YouTuber MrBeast's #TeamTrees movement, which has raised millions to plant trees |date=November 20, 2019 |work=[[Business Insider]] |access-date=December 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Top donations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Rank\n! scope=\"col\" | Donation ([[U.S. dollar|USD]])\n! scope=\"col\" | Donor